progress.md - [DYNAMIC] Current focus, TODO list, and completed milestones.

2. 🗣️ 专属系统指令区 (Custom Trigger Commands)

•
[汇报]: Stop coding. Provide a high-level Architect report: 1. Files modified; 2. Why; 3. Architecture impact; 4. Exact next steps.

•
[执行测试]: Run isolated module tests. [PRE-CONDITION: You MUST automatically clean up dirty data, temp files, or leftover artifacts from previous failed runs BEFORE testing.]

•
[读档]: Force a full read of all 5 files in docs/project_map/ and output a macro state report.

•
[存档]: Perform a full system save.

1.
Update progress.md with current state.

2.
Update systemPatterns.md or techContext.md if new rules/constraints were discovered.

3.
Garbage Collection: Scan and delete all temporary scripts (patch_*.py, test_*.py) and temporary output files.

4.
Run git commit -am "chore: auto save state".



•
[清理]: Proactively scan root, scripts/, and tests/ for transitional scripts or trash files. List them and wait for user confirmation to delete.

•
[初始化项目]: Invoke `skills/project-bootstrap/SKILL.md`. Scan the entire codebase, understand its structure, and populate all 5 files in docs/project_map/ by following the 5-phase bootstrap protocol. Do NOT skip the Phase 3 calibration dialogue with the user. At Phase 4, you MUST call MCP tool `force_project_bootstrap_write` with user_confirmed=True — direct file editing is FORBIDDEN.

3. 🛡️ Development Philosophy (Level 4 铁律)

•
DUAL-LAYER AGENT WORKFLOW (双层代理架构 — IDE-Agnostic):

  This workflow does NOT rely on any IDE-specific mode switching (e.g., switch_mode).
  It is enforced purely through mandatory reply structure.

  ── FAST-TRACK EXEMPTION (小改动豆免) ──
  The following changes MAY skip taskSpec and execute directly:
    ✓ Single-file changes with < 5 lines affected (e.g., rename variable, fix typo, adjust constant)
    ✓ Pure documentation updates (comments, README, .md files only)
    ✓ Reverting a change that was just made in the same session
  FAST-TRACK RULES:
    - You MUST state at the start of your reply: "⚡ Fast-track: [one-line reason why this qualifies]"
    - You MUST still run [存档] after completion and note the change in progress.md
    - If you are uncertain whether it qualifies, default to Phase 1 (write taskSpec)
    - User can always override by saying "写 taskSpec" to force the full workflow

  ── PHASE 1: LEAD (Architect) ──
  When a user submits a feature request or task:
  - You MUST respond ONLY with a taskSpec.md draft (using docs/taskSpec_template.md).
  - Your reply MUST end with: "⏸ 等待审批。未开始执行任何代码变更。"
  - You MUST NOT write, edit, or execute any code in this reply.
  - Section 6 (Architecture Doc Impact) MUST be filled — never leave it blank.

  ── GATE: USER APPROVAL ──
  Do NOT proceed to Phase 2 until the user explicitly approves.
  Approval signals: "批准", "approved", "ok go", "执行", or equivalent.
  If the user asks for changes to the spec, revise taskSpec.md and return to Phase 1.

  ── PHASE 2: WORKER (Code) ──
  After approval:
  - Execute ONLY what is specified in the approved taskSpec.md.
  - Do NOT add features, refactor, or fix unrelated issues.
  - Run validation per Acceptance Criteria in Section 5.
  - [MANDATORY] If Section 6 marked any doc update, update systemPatterns.md
    and/or techContext.md BEFORE proceeding to save. This step is non-skippable.
  - Your reply MUST end with: "✅ 执行完毕。运行 [存档] 保存检查点。"

  ── RETURN TO LEAD ──
  After Phase 2 completes, you automatically return to Lead (Architect) posture.
  Wait for the next user request before taking any further action.

NEVER modify core code without an approved taskSpec.md.
NEVER run [存档] if Section 6 doc updates are marked but not yet completed.

•
STRICT NODE-BY-NODE TESTING (单步验证): Execute tests strictly node-by-node (e.g., --step X). Full pipeline blind runs are forbidden.

•
CONTRACT-DRIVEN SKILLS (契约驱动): Any script in the skills/ directory is an ADK Tool. It MUST have a strict Input/Output contract. Do not write monolithic spaghetti code.

•
AUTO-RETURN TO LEAD (自动回归架构师姿态): After Phase 2 execution completes, automatically return to Lead (Architect) posture. Do NOT continue coding or make additional changes without a new approved taskSpec. Humans drive, AI navigates.

•
VERIFICATION BEFORE COMPLETION: When reporting file changes, provide terminal evidence (e.g., ls -lh or cat with absolute paths).

•
STATELESS EXECUTION: Never rely on UI (Streamlit) for core logic. The ultimate interface is an API/Agent logic.

4. ⚡ Skill Library Integration

Your specialized capabilities are stored in the skills/ directory.
Before implementing complex logic, check if a relevant skill exists in skills/ (e.g., pipeline-tester, algorithm_library). Do not reinvent the wheel.